                  <tr>
                     <td valign="top" class="TableCellAlternate">
                        Customers who have purchased a copy of the Earthdawn Player's Compendium from DriveThruRPG.com should now haved received notification
                        of a PDF update. This brings the eBook in line with the forthcoming print edition and includes the majority of the errata
                        and feedback we have received to date. <b>It is possible you may have downloaded a cached copy. The date of this publication,
                        at the bottom of p. 2, is "January 2006--First Printing"; if it says anything else, you will need to redownload from DTRPG.</b>
                        If you have purchased a copy of the Player's Compendium, please make sure that your DriveThruRPG.com account is updated to
                        provide notifications. We will be resetting the FAQs soon to remove extraneous entries and formal Errata will be available
                        from the Downloads, Free Stuff as a PDF document.<br/><br/>
                        
                     </td>
                  </tr>
